The paper proposes a multi-task spatio-temporal network for saliency estimation, action recognition, and video summarization. These tasks are all related to computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.MM). The paper also mentions the use of attention modules, which are commonly used in deep learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on multiple datasets, which involves information retrieval (cs.IR).
